item.title: heatherwiththebeck on Instagram [VIDEO]
item.description: Was just composing a mini-essay about fear (for the Patreon ‚Äî link in bio). We literally, all of us, have a big fear. Don‚Äôt be macho. You know you do, too. Snakes are cool. I like them, actually. In Spain, there are about a dozen that are dangerous. About a year ago, when it was dry and the critters came near the house, I felled a legit asp. Fucking felt like a badass. If you can‚Äôt take the heat, get out of the kitchen! Those fuckers are everywhere. Like one of those old ladies from ‚ÄúMad Max: Fury Road.‚Äù But with wasps, and not cartoonish hypermasculinity. Which brings me to my last remaining fear that I have. At least for the time being. As a certain lady (who I posted about on Patreon yesterday) has pointed out... vertigo. Yeah! So what?! Really high places are the devil, and I have a healthy sense of self preservation. Yup. Sticking to it. Though... she did say she would do something really special/neat for/to me if I stood on this one particular wall... There might be rum involved? Sooo... we‚Äôll see. üòè
